[
  {
    "id": "cloche-zbm",
    "title": "Orchestration loop: split into list-tasks, main, finalize phases",
    "description": "Rework the daemon's orchestration loop to use three distinct workflow phases instead of a single host.cloche main workflow:\n\n1. list-tasks: Pre-main workflow that outputs available work as JSONL (one task per line). Each line has id, status, title, description, and optional metadata. Status is one of open/closed/in-progress. cloched parses this output natively.\n\n2. main: The user-defined 'do the work' workflow. Receives a task ID (via env var) from the daemon. The workflow is responsible for actually claiming the ticket.\n\n3. finalize: Post-main workflow that runs after main completes, on BOTH success and failure. Handles cleanup, merging, pushing for review, etc. The workflow decides what to do based on outcome.\n\nThe daemon orchestrates: load tasks via list-tasks, pick open task(s), spawn main with task ID, run finalize when main completes. Replaces the current timed/capped loop approach."
  }
]
